metadata.name: Ersbla #341
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: Wood Wooden #175
metadata.description:
It was a sudden spark in my mind after losing a game of Jenga. When placed next to each other, the regular pieces of Jenga create interesting designs. But they were not perfect and there had to be changes to them. Thinking it was boring, I took the dog for a walk. Goldie's favorite shop was the animal toy shop. When I entered the store, seeing the toys of different animals, especially birds, and their coloring, as well as putting them together, the idea of arranging the pieces of Jenga was complete for me.

I needed a wooden board with a classic arrangement and decoration in colors and shapes.

Looking at the arrangements in the classic style, I tried to put pieces of wood with warm and vibrant colors and soft and tonal colors together in a frame. To keep the design simple, I did not use many geometric shapes and mostly used squares and rectangles whose edges are rounded at different angles.

100% Code
Made by p5.js

metadata.name: The Age of Automata #5
metadata.description:
This is an exploration of cellular automaton to find simplicity and beauty in mathematics.

First, a grid with random dimensions is created. A color palette is randomly selected from a large number of palettes, and a cellular automaton is formed based on one of the rules, and this operation may be repeated randomly to form a relatively more complex pattern. Finally, a number of geometries are combined with the automaton to make the mint harmonious and unique.

The idea was inspired by discoveries of Wolfram and Ciphrdâ€™s artwork.

metadata.description:

A giveaway/gift for the new year 2024!

Happy new year to all !!

CONTROLS

metadata.name: Polyptych #54
metadata.description:
Polyptych is a 3D interactive installation inspired by generative plotter designs. It is also meant to be displayed as multiple prints taken from different angles, be it a diptych, triptych, tetraptych, or more.

For an example see: https://bgo.la/polyptych.png

Instructions:

- use the mouse to navigate around the piece (zoom, pan and drag)
- press 'c' to switch between multiple camera angles
- press 'space' to pause the animation
- press 'p' to take a screenshot in a custom resolution (always 1:1 ratio) of the current view. Note that taking a screenshot will only work when seeing the piece live (click 'Open live' on fxhash), not on the mint page because of the sandboxed iframe.

Berlin, December 2021
@bgola

metadata.name: Balanced #245
metadata.description:
What does balance look like when viewed through the lens of pure mathematics? This is the question Balanced attempts to answer.

Each output is composed of a unique collection of blocks mathematically stacked to be in perfect balance.

This is my Genesis project. Enjoy!

Interactions:
1 - Reverse your stack vertically and re-balance.
2 - Toggle between square and portrait frame.
3 - Show center of mass. 
4 - Toggle the border.
5 - Toggle the background (color/transparent)
6 - Export image (2048x2048)
7 - Export image (4096x4096)
8 - Export image (8192x8192)

How it was made: https://www.jeffweber.art/balanced

metadata.name: Life has no scores #195
metadata.description:
We cannot compose life, at best we hum along to the melodies that life has been played in front of us. Looking back at the scores of our lives, the notations are never neatly noted, but fully felt.  Rewinding the songs of life are our memories, whether sad, happy, angry, or melancholy. It is not clear whether I am dreaming or awake, but our songs all do end. 

In this final drop (for ?), I have reused the first ever class calligraphy(){} I have written from my genesis drop â€œNothing comes from nothingâ€. As time passes, 10 drops later, across almost to the year, I am grateful for the progress I have made, as an artist, and more importantly as a human. After all, what is behind the code of generative art is a human being. 

Scores of music, scrolls of calligraphy, calendar or diary, notating life, time passes, and changes are inevitable. Sometimes we sing louder in laughter and joy, sometimes we scribble in uneasiness, sometimes we just get lost in neon lights. Life goes on. You and me, all the same and yet different.  

There are too many friend artists, friend collectors, fxhash team members, to thank for helping me through this journey. I would like to pay homage to Rudxane in this work, who has taken me under his wings, mentoring and encouraging me in art as well as showing me some degen stuff on the side:-). This homage is not copy-minting, or copying of styles, which I do not have the coding skills to do so even if I wanted to. But it is the influence of taste in many works of Rudxane. In a vague but agreeable taste, I present to you Life has no scores. 

What I was taught was disrupted, and grid studies left unfinished, and oh do we have a BINGO?

Tested on Chrome. Other browsers may render different or not at all (firefox)

Press â€˜2â€™ to save png.
